SIMPLE: parget
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Parget
<hw>Par"get</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Pargeted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Pargeting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>pargeten</ets>, also
<ets>spargeten</ets>, <ets>sparchen</ets>; of uncertain origin.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To coat with parget; to plaster, as walls, or the
interior of flues; <as>as, to <ex>parget</ex> the outside of their
houses</as>.</def> <rj><au>Sir T. Herbert.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>pargeted</qex> ceiling with pendants.</q> <rj><qau>R. L.
Stevenson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To paint; to cover over.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Parget</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Parget
<hw>Par"get</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To lay on
plaster.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To paint, as the face.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>B. Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Parget</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Parget
<hw>Par"get</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Gypsum or plaster
stone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Plaster, as for lining the interior of flues, or for
stuccowork.</def> <rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Paint, especially for the face.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Drayton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pargeter</ent>⟦br⟧
